As part of the more recent API work (version 3+) the HubSpot API pretty much always passes record id values as strings. With this in mind it seems there is a bug in the associations v4<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/crm/associations| batch read endpoint>:
`/crm/v4/associations/{fromObjectType}/{toObjectType}/batch/read`

The API documentation correctly reports that the "toObjectId" property will present string values. I am finding that it returns numeric (integer) values, example response:
``` {
  "status": "COMPLETE",
  "results": [
    {
      "to": [
        {
          "toObjectId": 22208856474,
          "associationTypes": [
            {
              "label": "Primary",
              "typeId": 1,
              "category": "HubSpot_DEFINED"
            },
            {
              "label": null,
              "typeId": 279,
              "category": "HubSpot_DEFINED"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "from": {
        "id": "46245548422"
      }
    }
  ],
  "startedAt": "2024-10-11T07:07:12.603Z",
  "completedAt": "2024-10-11T07:07:12.637Z"
}```
The use of numeric IDs will cause issues in NodeJS /browser environments if the ID is a full range int64 value, hence the need to use strings.

Is this the best place to report the issue?
